# Course 1: Foundations – Data, Data Everywhere (22 hours)

**Course overview:** This course onboards beginners to data analytics, its roles, lifecycle, and ethics. Each module applies the Learn Your Way two-step pipeline: personalization to grade level and interest, then synchronized representations: immersive text with embedded questions, narrated slide outlines with speaker notes, an audio teacher–student script, and a mind map. Section-level quizzes supply Glows and Grows feedback and adapt difficulty in later items.    ([Google Research][1])

**Why this structure:** Learn Your Way’s randomized controlled study shows significantly higher immediate and three-day retention versus a standard digital reader when learners study with personalized, multi-view content and embedded formative assessment. Embedded questions and section quizzes close the loop with targeted feedback labeled as Glows and Grows.

**Hours and sequencing:**

* Module 1: 6 hours
* Module 2: 6 hours
* Module 3: 6 hours
* Module 4: 4 hours
* Capstone: included inside the 22 hours as the last 2 of the total in Module 4’s window

**Tools introduced but light-touch only:** Sheets or Excel, SQL sandbox, Tableau viewer, RStudio preview, GitHub viewing. This mirrors the toolchain used in the Google Data Analytics Certificate pathway. ([Grow with Google][2])

---

## Module table: titles, hours, objectives, prerequisites, success criteria

| Module | Title                                      | Hours | Objectives                                                                                                 | Prereqs | Success criteria                                                                                          |
| ------ | ------------------------------------------ | ----: | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------- | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| C1-M1  | The Data Ecosystem and Roles               |     6 | Explain the analytics lifecycle, distinguish analyst vs BI vs data scientist, describe common data sources | None    | Accurately describe roles and lifecycle, identify suitable data sources for a prompt                      |
| C1-M2  | Analytical Thinking and Question Design    |     6 | Write SMART questions, map stakeholder goals to metrics, practice structured problem framing               | C1-M1   | Produce a question backlog and hypothesis list that passes instructor checklist                           |
| C1-M3  | The Analyst’s Toolbox                      |     6 | Compare Sheets, SQL, Tableau, R; complete first interactive lab in each                                    | C1-M1   | Execute a SELECT on a sample DB, build a pivot table, open a Tableau workbook, knit an R Markdown preview |
| C1-M4  | Ethics, Privacy, and Professional Practice |     4 | Recognize bias, fairness, and privacy risks; draft a lightweight data ethics SOP                           | C1-M1   | Submit an ethics checklist and risk log for a toy dataset, pass scenario quiz 80 percent+                 |

