**Readable rendering:** You will operationalize ethics with a simple SOP and show that you can balance privacy with utility through aggregation and suppression.

---

## Course 1 capstone: Personal Learning Roadmap

**Description:** Build a 1 to 2 page roadmap that states your target analyst role, the three skills you will prioritize, the datasets you will use for practice, and the exact artifacts you will ship in later courses. Tie each skill to an assessment plan.

**Expected artifacts:**

* Roadmap PDF and a short 2-slide deck, plus a one-paragraph GitHub README.
* Links to one dataset you plan to use from Kaggle or Google Dataset Search.
* A self-quiz plan: 10 questions you will answer at the end of Phase 2.
  This capstone closes the loop on personalization and sets up multi-view learning, consistent with the Learn Your Way approach of synchronized modalities and embedded assessment.

**Grading for Course 1 only:**

* Adaptive quizzes: 20 percent
* Hands-on labs bundle: 30 percent
* Capstone roadmap: 30 percent
* Presentation of roadmap: 20 percent
  Use Glows and Grows comments on each submission to guide iteration.

---

## Delivery notes for platforms

* **Bind the views:** Render immersive text by section; place a “Switch view” control to jump to narrated slides, audio dialogue, or mind map of the same content. This mirrors Learn Your Way’s synchronized representations pattern.
* **Formative assessment:** Enable embedded questions inline and a section-level quiz that returns a score plus Glows and Grows, then adjust the next item’s difficulty.
* **Tool parity with Google pathway:** Ensure learners can open sample Tableau workbooks, run basic SQL queries, and preview an R Markdown, matching the stack in Google’s Data Analytics Certificate. ([Grow with Google][2])

---

